    • Uses of IChangeHistoryDescriptor in com.ibm.team.scm.client

      Methods in com.ibm.team.scm.client that return IChangeHistoryDescriptor 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      IChangeHistoryDescriptor IChangeHistory.getHistoryDescriptor(boolean requireStateHandles, org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
      Returns a data structure which describes the current state of history, including the list of change sets made in the era of this change history as well as a reference to the previous change history if one exists.
      Methods in com.ibm.team.scm.client that return types with arguments of type IChangeHistoryDescriptor 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List<IChangeHistoryDescriptor> IChangeHistory.getHistoryDescriptors(int numberOfChangeSets, boolean requireStateHandles, org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
      Returns a list of data structures describing the current state of this era and its predecessors, including enough eras to span the given number of change sets if the history is long enough.
